Luckily I was was able to enjoy a @noblecigars for breakfast at @rondevucigarlounge before they were completely sold out within a day!! 
No worries more are on the way to my favorite lounge! 
I paired my cigar early in the morning with a caramel macchiato and some banana nut bread. The sweetness I was getting from the cigar totally hid the fact that I was smoking a double ligero. All I was tasting was sweet honey notes throughout my smoke with a light spice when lighting the cigar. What made my experience even more enjoyable was admiring the construction on the full bodied Act 1. Beautiful white smoke flowed out paired with an amazing white ash. I hope you get to enjoy your Noble Cigar soon!

Visited @thekingcigarlounge in DTLA. I thought I was going to walk in there and everyone was going to be snobby and I was going to be ignored…this is why we don’t make assumptions lol. I walked into the lounge and was immediately greeted by Frank and invited into the humidor. After chatting with Frank and picking out some cigars he gave us a tour of this beautiful lounge. Frank served us up some tequilas and made sure we were good throughout our stay. These are the kind of lounges that make a difference for our lounge experiences and in the cigar community. I’m not really a lounge girl but I will gladly keep visiting The Kings Lounge….
